,{"id":115435,"date":631065600,"human":"1989","platform":{"id":63,"name":"Atari ST/STE"},"release_region":{"id":1,"region":"europe"}}],"screenshots":[{"id":77018,"image_id":"vq62lka0suykmscjcm5p","url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/vq62lka0suykmscjcm5p.jpg"},{"id":710306,"image_id":"scf82q","url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/scf82q.jpg"},{"id":710307,"image_id":"scf82r","url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/scf82r.jpg"},{"id":710305,"image_id":"scf82p","url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/scf82p.jpg"}],"similar_games":[119207,27378,43367,23314,47161,3772,56033,118871,15851,112078],"slug":"power-drift","summary":"Power Drift is a kart racing game released in arcades by Sega in 1988. More technologically advanced than Sega's earlier 2.5D racing games, like Hang-On (1985) and Out Run (1986), in Power Drift the entire world and track consist of sprites. The upgraded hardware of the Sega Y Board allows individual sprites and the background to be rotated\u2013even while being scaled\u2013making the visuals more dynamic.\n\nDesigned and directed by Yu Suzuki, the game was a critical and commercial success upon release in arcades. It was subsequently ported to various home computers in Europe by Activision in 1989, followed by a PC Engine port published in Japan by Asmik Ace in 1990. It was not released on Sega consoles until the Sega Ages release for the Sega Saturn in 1998.","total_rating":72.09570706829739,"total_rating_count":8,"url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/power-drift","videos":[{"id":63393,"video_id":"fHwU5JrvcIg"}],"websites":[{"id":257627,"url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Power_Drift","type":{"id":3,"type":"Wikipedia"}},{"id":356528,"url":"https://www.twitch.tv/directory/game/Power%20Drift","type":{"id":6,"type":"Twitch"}}]}